						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vijaya Gaṇḍagōpāladēva. Year 19: A.D. 1269.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gift of 5 cows for a twilight lamp <hi rend="italic">(chandhi viḷakku)</hi> to be lighted in the temple of Tiru-Iḷambayaṅkōṭṭūr in Kaṉṟūr-nāḍu, a subdivision of Maṇaviṟ-kōṭṭam in Jayaṅkoṇḍachōḻa-maṇḍalam by Kulōttuṅgachōḻachchambuvarāyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Aḻagiyachōḻaṉ. Two groups of <hi rend="italic">brāhmaṇas</hi> belonging to the cow shed <hi rend="italic">(gōmaḍam)</hi> of the temple received the cows and agreed to maintain the lamp for 15 days each.</p>						

						</summary>
